while a > cumsum(T_a(Index_a(end,1),1:i))
is the same as
while all(a > cumsum(T_a(Index_a(end,1),1:i)))
so you can translate this to Python as
while np.all(a > np.cumsum(T_a[Index_a[-1,0],(0,i-1)])):
But do note that, if T_a is non-negative, this can be simplified, because the first element of the cumsum result will be the smallest one, and equal to the first element of its input. So you’d need to compare only against that element:
while a > T_a(Index_a(end,1),1)

